# UI and Design System Rules

- Preserve Gugugram's retro Windows 95 visual style in new UI work.
- Use tokens from `src/styles/global.css`; avoid introducing raw hex colors in components.
- Prefer existing utility classes and `_ui` primitives before adding new bespoke CSS.
- Use `.astro` for static/SSR rendering and `.svelte` for client interactivity.
- Follow Svelte 5 runes patterns in Svelte components (`$props`, `$state`, `$derived`, `$bindable`).

## Component Organization

- Keep component structure as `ComponentName/ComponentName.svelte` or `.astro`.
- Keep reusable primitives under `src/components/_ui/`.
- Avoid modern visual patterns that break the retro style (rounded modern cards, soft shadows).
